CCM Investment Advisers LLC Invests $392,000 in Manitowoc Food Service, Inc. (WBT)


					Posted by Harper Lund on Jul 19th, 2017 // No Comments




CCM Investment Advisers LLC bought a new position in  Manitowoc Food Service, Inc. (NYSE:WBT) during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the SEC. The institutional investor  bought 20,000 shares of the industrial products company’s stock, valued at approximately $392,000. 
Several other institutional investors also recently modified their holdings of the company. Public Employees Retirement Association of Colorado bought a new position in shares of  Manitowoc Food Service during the first quarter worth $625,000.  Baird Financial Group Inc. acquired a new stake in  Manitowoc Food Service during the first quarter worth about $234,000.  State of Wisconsin Investment Board acquired a new stake in  Manitowoc Food Service during the first quarter worth about $9,315,000.  Russell Investments Group Ltd. acquired a new stake in  Manitowoc Food Service during the first quarter worth about $3,956,000.  Finally, Nationwide Fund Advisors acquired a new stake in  Manitowoc Food Service during the first quarter worth about $2,180,000. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own  86.86% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Manitowoc Food Service Inc. alerts:



Shares of Manitowoc Food Service, Inc. (NYSE WBT) opened at 19.49 on Wednesday. The stock has a 50 day moving average of $19.16 and a 200 day moving average of $19.34. Manitowoc Food Service, Inc. has a 52 week low of $14.93 and a 52 week high of $21.13. The stock has a market cap of $2.71 billion, a P/E ratio of 40.60 and a beta of 2.29. 





Manitowoc Food Service (NYSE:WBT) last announced its quarterly earnings results on Monday, May 8th. The industrial products company reported $0.08 earnings per share for the quarter, missing the consensus estimate of $0.09 by $0.01. The firm had revenue of $328 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $318.12 million. Manitowoc Food Service had a net margin of 4.55% and a negative return on equity of 121.38%. Manitowoc Food Service’s revenue for the quarter was up .8% on a year-over-year basis.  On average, analysts expect that  Manitowoc Food Service, Inc. will post $0.72 earnings per share for the current year. 
COPYRIGHT VIOLATION WARNING: “CCM Investment Advisers LLC Invests $392,000 in Manitowoc Food Service, Inc. (WBT)” was  reported by Chaffey Breeze and is the sole property of of Chaffey Breeze. If you are viewing this news story on another website, it was illegally copied and republished in violation of US & international copyright legislation. The correct version of this news story can be viewed at https://www.chaffeybreeze.com/2017/07/19/20000-shares-in-manitowoc-food-service-inc-wbt-acquired-by-ccm-investment-advisers-llc-updated-updated-updated.html. 
A number of equities research analysts recently issued reports on the stock. Zacks Investment Research raised shares of Manitowoc Food Service from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating and set a $23.00 price target on the stock in a research note on Wednesday, May 10th. Barclays PLC increased their target price on shares of Manitowoc Food Service from $19.00 to $20.00 and gave the company an “equal weight” rating in a research note on Wednesday, April 19th. Two investment analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and three have given a buy rating to the company’s stock. The company currently has a consensus rating of “Buy” and a consensus price target of $21.20.
In related news, SVP Joel H. Horn sold 1,561 shares of the business’s stock in a transaction dated Wednesday, June 14th. The shares were sold at an average price of $19.23, for a total value of $30,018.03. Following the sale, the senior vice president now directly owns 3,515 shares in the company, valued at approximately $67,593.45. The sale was disclosed in a legal filing with the SEC, which can be accessed through this link. 0.67% of the stock is currently owned by insiders. 
Manitowoc Food Service Company Profile
Welbilt, Inc, formerly Manitowoc Foodservice, Inc, is a commercial foodservice equipment company. The Company designs, manufactures and supplies food and beverage equipment for the global commercial foodservice market, offering customers operator and patron insights, kitchen solutions, culinary expertise, and implementation support and service.







