					Posted by Oliver Carreras on Jul 26th, 2017 // No Comments




Amalgamated Bank purchased a new stake in shares of  Manitowoc Food Service, Inc. (NYSE:WBT) during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the SEC. The institutional investor  purchased 18,276 shares of the industrial products company’s stock, valued at approximately $359,000. 
A number of other large investors also recently bought and sold shares of WBT. Nisa Investment Advisors LLC acquired a new stake in  Manitowoc Food Service during the first quarter valued at approximately $120,000.  Teacher Retirement System of Texas purchased a new position in  Manitowoc Food Service during the first quarter valued at $203,000.  Jacobus Wealth Management Inc. bought a new position in  Manitowoc Food Service during the first quarter worth $207,000.  Group One Trading L.P. bought a new position in  Manitowoc Food Service during the first quarter worth $208,000.  Finally, Leavell Investment Management Inc. bought a new position in  Manitowoc Food Service during the first quarter worth $221,000. 86.86% of the stock is owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 


 Get Manitowoc Food Service Inc. alerts:



