Manitowoc Food Service (NYSE:WBT) last issued its quarterly earnings data on Monday, May 8th. The industrial products company reported $0.08 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.09 by $0.01. The business had revenue of $328 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $318.12 million. Manitowoc Food Service had a negative return on equity of 121.38% and a net margin of 4.55%. Manitowoc Food Service’s revenue for the quarter was up .8% on a year-over-year basis.  On average, equities analysts predict that  Manitowoc Food Service, Inc. will post $0.72 EPS for the current year. 
